ðŸ”¹ String Questions for Coding Interviews
1. Basic String Manipulation

Reverse a string without using library functions.

Check if a string is a palindrome.

Count vowels and consonants in a string.

Convert the first letter of each word to uppercase.

Remove all duplicates from a string.

Find the frequency of each character in a string.

Remove all white spaces from a string.

Check if two strings are anagrams.

Find the first non-repeating character in a string.

Implement your own substring() function.

2. Two Pointers / Sliding Window

Longest substring without repeating characters.

Check if a string contains a permutation of another string.

Minimum window substring that contains all characters of another string.

Longest palindromic substring.

Smallest substring with all unique characters.

Count substrings with exactly k distinct characters.

Find all anagram indices of a pattern in a string.

Longest substring with at most k distinct characters.

3. Pattern Matching & Searching

Implement strStr() (find index of substring).

KMP Algorithm for pattern searching.

Rabin-Karp Algorithm for substring search.

Z-algorithm for pattern searching.

Find the longest prefix which is also a suffix.

4. Recursion & Backtracking

Print all permutations of a string.

Generate all subsets of a string.

Generate all valid parenthesis strings of length n.

Word break problem (split string into dictionary words).

Restore IP addresses from a string.

5. Advanced / Tricky

Find the longest repeating subsequence.

Check if two strings are isomorphic.

Encode and decode strings (like LeetCode 271).

Implement string compression (e.g., aaabb â†’ a3b2).

Multiply two numbers given as strings.

Add binary strings.

Longest common prefix in an array of strings.

Print all palindromic substrings of a string.
